    "objective": "“We performed a population pharmacokinetic analysis of phenytoin after intravenous administration of fosphenytoin sodium in healthy, neurosurgical, and epileptic subjects, including pediatric patients, and determined the optimal dose and infusion rate for achieving the therapeutic range”",
    "covariates": "Tested: WT AGE< SEX< and trial patient type on all parameters Included: WT on CL, V2, V3",
    "observations": "Simulations are provided that show the impact of dosing regimen and thereby allow optimisation of target achievement. Atypical allometry was used, possibly due to the inclusion of young children, for which otherwise a maturation function may be needed",
    "dose": "Steady-state IV doses in healthy subjects and patients",
    "structure": "2-compartment model with zero-order infusion of fosphenytoin sodium into a compartment with first-order absorption (transformation to phenytoin) and first-order elimination of phenytoin",
